 RIVERS State Government has asked all public and private schools to resume on Monday with strict adherence to Coronavirus protocols. The Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Education, Chidi Adiele, said the resumption date was in line with the school calendar published in August 2020 by Governor, Nyesom Wike. Adiele ordered all the schools to maintain all the COVID-19 protocols, such as wearing face masks, use of hand sanitizers and maintenance of physical distancing.